author: Nic White For Daily Mail Australia
title: Sydney bracing for torrential rain and flash flooding | Daily Mail Online
text: Here we go again: Sydney to be hit with ANOTHER round of torrential rain and flash flooding at peak hour - after morning deluge turns roads into rivers Huge thunderstorms battered Sydney causing flash flooding across the city Weather bureau issued severe thunderstorm warning on Tuesday morning About 48mm fell in an hour, more than all of January - wettest day since winter SES is rescuing people trapped by floodwaters and warning against driving Traffic is thrown into chaos and light rail services are cancelled by floods Another up to 50mm expected overnight to double what fell during the day Published: 04:26 GMT, 7 February 2017 | Updated: 09:43 GMT, 7 February 2017 378 shares
